      "name": "Absolute hemolysis index validation — FDA pump 5-point sweep",
      "description": "ValidationResult comparing CFD-predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values against in-vitro measurements across 5 flow-speed operating points. Mean absolute error 0.0043 g/100L; all predictions within 12% of experimental mean. Validation was executed under ModelConfiguration ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7-rc2, which the simulation team characterised as 'effectively the same build' as the released version 2026-q1-build-7 because only a documentation patch was applied between the release candidate and the final tag. No re-run of the validation suite was performed under the released build.",
      "wasGeneratedBy": {
        "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/modelconfig/ansys-cfx-15-rc2",
        "type": "ModelConfiguration",
        "name": "ANSYS CFX 15 — 2026-Q1 release candidate build",
        "modelVersion": "ansys-cfx-15-build-2026-q1-build-7-rc2",
        "description": "Release-candidate solver configuration used during the validation campaign. Solver settings, turbulence model (SST k-omega), hemolysis power-law constants, and mesh topology are identical to the production build; the only change between rc2 and the final tag was an update to internal release notes and a version-string increment in the solver banner. The simulation team concluded that re-executing the 72-hour validation sweep was unnecessary given the trivial nature of the delta."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/hemolysis-uq-monte-carlo-02",
